      "beat_id": "B14",
      "t_start": 129,
      "estimated_duration_s": 12,
      "narration_text": "What forces the statistics when electrons have no force between them? Antisymmetry writes a zero along the diagonal — they cannot share a point. One sign separates matter's structure from its collapse. QUANTUM MECHANICS.",
